
Overview of noun vanity

The noun vanity has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (4) amour propre, conceit, self-love, vanity -- (feelings of excessive pride)
2. vanity, emptiness -- (the quality of being valueless or futile; "he rejected the vanities of the world")
3. conceit, conceitedness, vanity -- (the trait of being unduly vain and conceited; false pride)
4. dressing table, dresser, vanity, toilet table -- (low table with mirror or mirrors where one sits while dressing or applying makeup)
